
Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Yes' radio button from 'Contrast enhanced' in Page 03 of Thoracic CT
And	I go to Page 05 of Thoracic CT
And I select 'Finding' radio button
And I select 'Nodule' from the dropdown menu
And I select 'I know' radio button

When I click on 'Characterization II' tab
Then 'Rigler notch sign' checkbox is enabled
And 'Eccentric necrosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Central necrosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fat' checkbox is enabled
And 'Calcification' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cavitation' checkbox is enabled

And 'Pleural finger' checkbox is enabled
And 'Corona radiata/spiculae' checkbox is enabled
And 'Halo sign' checkbox is enabled
And 'Associated atelectasis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Reversed halo sign (central GGO surrounded by in-/complete ring of consolidation)' checkbox is enabled

And 'None' radio button is enabled
And 'Minimal' radio button is enabled
And 'Marked' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Minimal' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Marked' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled
